I am a British Chinese living in London UK and have just returned from China. I won't discuss the political stances or who is right or wrong here; I'll just share my feelings about returning to China after seven years.

The environment is much cleaner than before, even cleaner than major cities in Europe. There are no more homeless beggars, unlike in the major cities in Europe where the subway stations are filthy with various excrements and crowded with homeless people.

People's behavior has greatly improved. On the bus, I saw people giving up their seats for the young and old, and they were not noisy in public places. Littering is rare on the streets, and people are willing to help others.

Transportation costs in China are extremely low. The transportation costs in London are exorbitant and hard to bear, and they increase every year.

There is an abundance of goods and a wide variety of delicious food, which is also very cheap. You can buy things and have them delivered even in the middle of the night. Europe and the UK lag far behind in this aspect.

The hotels are of a very high standard, yet the prices are very low.

If I retire in the future, I would choose to live in China.
